</p>
<p>Hold command and open <code>getLastAuthenticationError()</code>. Ultimately, this reads
a <code>Security::AUTHENTICATION_ERROR</code> string key from the session.</p>
<p>And the same is true for fetching the last username, or email in our case: it reads
a key from the session.</p>
<p>Here's the deal: the login form is automatically setting the authentication error
to the session for us. But, it is <em>not</em> setting the last username on the session...
because it doesn't really know where to look for it.</p>
<p>No worries, fix this with <code>$request-&gt;getSession()-&gt;set()</code> and pass it the constant -
<code>Security::LAST_USERNAME</code> - and <code>$data['_username']</code>:</p>
