<h2 id="adding-the-logout-key">Adding the logout Key <a class="headerlink" href="logout-and-last-username#adding-the-logout-key" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>Whaaaat? Yep, our controller will do nothing. Instead, Symfony will intercept any
requests to <code>/logout</code> and take care of everything for us. To activate it, open <code>security.yml</code>
and add a new key under your firewall: <code>logout</code>. Below that, add <code>path: /logout</code>:</p>
