	                            <div id="dsq-comment-text-2890756795" class="dsq-comment-text">
	                                <p>Be careful! You can failed with error when user IS null if you just checking `app.user.username ` Use extra check in if statement like:<br><code>{% if app.user and app.user.username %}</code></p><p>But probably `if app.user ` will be enough here, because for some weird reasons user could have no username but could be logged in. I mean, that app.user return an object <i>only</i> if a user is logged in. So you don't need username extra check here.</p><p>Cheers! </p>
