	                        <div id="dsq-comment-message-2890745157" class="dsq-comment-message">
	                            <div id="dsq-comment-text-2890745157" class="dsq-comment-text">
	                                <p>Hey Yang,</p><p>It's easy enough! You have access to the global context in Twig templates which allows to get currently logged in user with  `app.user`. So just use:<br></p><pre><code><br>&lt;li&gt;<br>  {% if app.user %}<br>    &lt;a href="{{ path('security_logout') }}&gt;Logout&lt;/a&gt;<br>  {% else %}<br>    &lt;a href="{{ path('security_login') }}&gt;Login&lt;/a&gt;<br>  {% endif%}<br>&lt;/li&gt;<br></code></pre><p></p><p>Cheers!</p>
	                            </div>
	                        </div>
